The paper introduces a new framework for learning with limited feedback, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The factored bandits model is a generalization of the rank-1 bandits model, which is a well-studied problem in the literature. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes an algorithm for solving the factored bandits problem, which involves techniques from optimization and decision theory. Therefore, the paper may also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper provides theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithm, which involves results from game theory and probability theory. Therefore, the paper may also be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
